25|$|In the Bailiwick of Jersey, {{there are}} <b>solicitors</b> (called ecrivains) <b>and</b> advocates (French avocat). In the Bailiwicks of Jersey and Guernsey {{and on the}} Isle of Man, Advocates perform the {{combined}} functions of both <b>solicitors</b> <b>and</b> <b>barristers.</b>|$|R
