5000|$|A {{pressure}} group called JABS (Justice, Awareness, Basic Support) {{was established to}} represent families with children who, their parents said, were [...] "vaccine-damaged". £15 million in public legal aid funding was spent on the litigation, of which £9.7 million went to <b>solicitors</b> <b>and</b> <b>barristers,</b> <b>and</b> £4.3 million to expert witnesses.|$|R
